android.permission.REQUEST_COMPANION_PRO.info: enables association with a device as a 'watch'.
android.permission.REQUEST_COMPANION_PRO.description: Allows app to request to be associated with a device via CompanionDeviceManager as a "watch".

android.permission.REQUEST_COMPANION_RUN.description: Allows a companion app to run in the background.

android.permission.REQUEST_COMPANION_USE.info: permits a companion app to use data in the background.
android.permission.REQUEST_COMPANION_USE.description: Allows a companion app to use data in the background.

android.permission.INTERNET.description: Allows an application to create network sockets.

android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the status of all networks.

android.permission.READ_CONTACTS.description: Allows an application to read all of the contact (address) data stored on your phone. Malicious applications can use this to send your data to other people.

android.permission.GET_ACCOUNTS.description: Allows access to the list of accounts in the Accounts Service.

android.permission.WAKE_LOCK.description: Allows an application to prevent the phone from going to sleep.

android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAG.description: Allows an application to write to external storage.

android.permission.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES.info: allows reading image files from external storage.
android.permission.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES.description: Allows an application to read image files from external storage.

android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE.description: Allows an application to read from external storage.

android.permission.SCHEDULE_EXACT_ALARM.info: permits exact alarm scheduling for background work.
android.permission.SCHEDULE_EXACT_ALARM.description: Allows an app to use exact alarm scheduling APIs to perform timing sensitive background work.

android.permission.RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETE.description: Allows an application to start itself as soon as the system has finished booting. This can make it take longer to start the phone and allow the application to slow down the overall phone by always running.

android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATIO.description: Access coarse location sources, such as the mobile network database, to determine an approximate phone location, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine approximately where you are.

android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION.description: Access fine location sources, such as the Global Positioning System on the phone, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine where you are and may consume additional battery power.

android.permission.ACCESS_BACKGROUND_LOC.description: Allows an app to access location in the background.

android.permission.READ_PHONE_NUMBERS.info: allows reading of the device's phone number(s).
android.permission.READ_PHONE_NUMBERS.description: Allows read access to the device's phone number(s). This is a subset of the capabilities granted by READ_PHONE_STATE but is exposed to instant applications.

android.permission.VIBRATE.description: Allows the application to control the vibrator.

android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE.description: Allows the application to access the phone features of the device. An application with this permission can determine the phone number and serial number of this phone, whether a call is active, the number that call is connected to and so on.

android.permission.ANSWER_PHONE_CALLS.info: permits an app to answer incoming phone calls.
android.permission.ANSWER_PHONE_CALLS.description: Allows the app to answer an incoming phone call.

android.permission.CALL_PHONE.description: Allows the application to call phone numbers without your intervention. Malicious applications may cause unexpected calls on your phone bill. Note that this does not allow the application to call emergency numbers.

android.permission.SEND_SMS.description: Allows application to send SMS messages. Malicious applications may cost you money by sending messages without your confirmation.

android.permission.BLUETOOTH.description: Allows applications to connect to paired bluetooth devices.

android.permission.BLUETOOTH_ADMIN.description: Allows applications to discover and pair bluetooth devices.

android.permission.BLUETOOTH_SCAN.info: required for discovering and pairing Bluetooth devices.
android.permission.BLUETOOTH_SCAN.description: Required to be able to discover and pair nearby Bluetooth devices.

android.permission.BLUETOOTH_CONNECT.info: necessary for connecting to paired Bluetooth devices.
android.permission.BLUETOOTH_CONNECT.description: Required to be able to connect to paired Bluetooth devices.

android.permission.READ_CALL_LOG.info: grants read access to the user's call log.
android.permission.READ_CALL_LOG.description: Allows an application to read the user's call log.

android.permission.READ_CALENDAR.description: Allows an application to read all of the calendar events stored on your phone. Malicious applications can use this to send your calendar events to other people.

android.permission.WRITE_CALENDAR.info: add or modify calendar events and send emails to guests
android.permission.WRITE_CALENDAR.description: Allows an application to add or change the events on your calendar, which may send emails to guests. Malicious applications can use this to erase or modify your calendar events or to send emails to guests.

android.permission.CAMERA.description: Allows application to take pictures and videos with the camera. This allows the application to collect images that the camera is seeing at any time.

android.permission.ACTIVITY_RECOGNITION.info: allow application to recognize physical activity
android.permission.ACTIVITY_RECOGNITION.description: Allows an application to recognize physical activity.

android.permission.USE_BIOMETRIC.info: allows use of device-supported biometric modalities.
android.permission.USE_BIOMETRIC.description: Allows an app to use device supported biometric modalities.

android.permission.USE_FINGERPRINT.description: This constant was deprecated in API level 28. Applications should request USE_BIOMETRIC instead.

android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE_CO.info: enables foreground services with connected device use.
android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE_CO.description: Allows a regular application to use Service.startForeground with the type "connectedDevice".

android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE_HE.info: enables foreground services with health-related functionality.
android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE_HE.description: Allows a regular application to use Service.startForeground with the type "health".

android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE_LO.info: allows foreground services with location use.
android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE_LO.description: Allows a regular application to use Service.startForeground with the type "location".

android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE_ME.info: enables foreground services for media playback.
android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE_ME.description: Allows a regular application to use Service.startForeground with the type "mediaPlayback".

android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE_RE.info: allows foreground services for remote messaging.
android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE_RE.description: Allows a regular application to use Service.startForeground with the type "remoteMessaging".

android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE_MI.info: permits foreground services with microphone use.
android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE_MI.description: Allows a regular application to use Service.startForeground with the type "microphone".

android.permission.RECORD_AUDIO.description: Allows application to access the audio record path.

android.permission.ACCESS_WIFI_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the information about the status of Wi-Fi.

android.permission.MODIFY_AUDIO_SETTINGS.description: Allows application to modify global audio settings, such as volume and routing.

android.permission.BROADCAST_STICKY.description: Allows an application to send sticky broadcasts, which remain after the broadcast ends. Malicious applications can make the phone slow or unstable by causing it to use too much memory.

android.permission.USE_FULL_SCREEN_INTEN.info: required for full screen intents in notifications.
android.permission.USE_FULL_SCREEN_INTEN.description: Required for apps targeting Build.VERSION_CODES.Q that want to use notification full screen intents.

metadata.cwe: CWE-532: Insertion of Sensitive Information into Log File
metadata.description: The App logs information. Sensitive information should never be logged.
This App uses SSL certificate pinning to detect or  prevent MITM attacks in secure communication channel.

metadata.cwe: CWE-312: Cleartext Storage of Sensitive Information
metadata.description: Files may contain hardcoded sensitive information like usernames, passwords, keys etc.

metadata.cwe: CWE-330: Use of Insufficiently Random Values
metadata.description: The App uses an insecure Random Number Generator.
App can read/write to External Storage. Any App can read data written to External Storage.

metadata.cwe: CWE-89: Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in an SQL Command ('SQL Injection')
metadata.description: App uses SQLite Database and execute raw SQL query. Untrusted user input in raw SQL queries can cause SQL Injection. Also sensitive information should be encrypted and written to the database.

metadata.cwe: CWE-649: Reliance on Obfuscation or Encryption of Security-Relevant Inputs without Integrity Checking
metadata.description: The App uses the encryption mode CBC with PKCS5/PKCS7 padding. This configuration is vulnerable to padding oracle attacks.
App creates temp file. Sensitive information should never be written into a temp file.

metadata.cwe: CWE-327: Use of a Broken or Risky Cryptographic Algorithm
metadata.description: SHA-1 is a weak hash known to have hash collisions.

metadata.cwe: CWE-327: Use of a Broken or Risky Cryptographic Algorithm
metadata.description: MD5 is a weak hash known to have hash collisions.
This App may have root detection capabilities.
This App copies data to clipboard. Sensitive data should not be copied to clipboard as other applications can access it.
IP Address disclosure

metadata.cwe: CWE-327: Use of a Broken or Risky Cryptographic Algorithm
metadata.description: The App uses ECB mode in Cryptographic encryption algorithm. ECB mode is known to be weak as it results in the same ciphertext for identical blocks of plaintext.

metadata.cwe: CWE-749: Exposed Dangerous Method or Function
metadata.description: Insecure WebView Implementation. Execution of user controlled code in WebView is a critical Security Hole.
Ensure that user controlled URLs never reaches the Webview. Enabling file access from URLs in WebView can leak sensitive information from the file system.

"snore_onboarding_policy_new" : "This feature helps you understand what interrupts your sleep and shows relevant insights and educational content.

How it works
When you wear your device to sleep and your microphone has been enabled on your device, this feature collects:

• Sound events, like coughing, to show when noise may have interrupted your sleep
• Snoring events, or how often snores are detected.

To give you a complete picture of sleep interruptions, your device collects this data every few seconds.

These sound events are used to determine if there is snoring in your environment but the audio recordings are not stored.

This data also helps Fitbit provide insights into your sleep and show relevant suggestions and educational content.

Managing your data
You can turn this feature off and download or delete your sleep data in Fitbit settings. Turning off this feature won't delete any existing data.

This feature is not intended to diagnose or treat any medical condition and should not be relied on for any medical purposes.

It is intended to provide information that can help you manage your wellbeing. If you have any concerns about your health, please talk to a healthcare provider."

"stress_onboarding_what_is" : "What is stress?
Stress is your body’s physical and emotional response to the demands of everyday life. When you’re stressed, you may get sweaty palms or a racing heart, but you might also notice changes in your emotions, like worry or excitement.

Where does it come from?
The source of stress can be positive, like a promotion or new baby, or negative, like an overwhelming workload or traumatic life event. It can also be triggered by illness, exercise, and different substances like caffeine.

Is it a bad thing?
Not necessarily! Small bursts of stress can motivate you to meet a deadline or avoid danger, but if it lasts for an extended period of time it can negatively affect your health and well-being."

"snore_onboarding_policy_gaia" : "This feature helps you understand what interrupts your sleep and shows relevant insights and educational content.

How it works
When you wear your device to sleep, this feature collects:

• Sound events, to show when noise may have interrupted your sleep
• Snoring events, or how often snores are detected.

To give you a complete picture of sleep interruptions, your device collects this data every few seconds.

Audio is used to determine sound and snoring events but audio is not stored and does not leave your device.

Sound and snoring events may be used to provide insights and educational content related to your sleep.

Managing your data
You can turn this feature off and download or delete your snore and noise detection data in Fitbit settings. Turning off this feature won't delete any existing data or disable microphone access for other voice-related features.

This feature is not intended to diagnose or treat any medical condition and should not be relied on for any medical purposes.

It is intended to provide information that can help you manage your wellbeing. If you have any concerns about your health, please talk to a healthcare provider."

"stress_help_responsiveness_description" : "When you’re stressed, the autonomic nervous system (ANS) releases hormones to prepare you for a “fight or flight” response. This process can raise your heart rate, change your skin’s sweat level and make you more alert or tense.

- Heart rate variability during deep sleep from the night before
- Elevated heart rate while at rest from the day before
- Sleeping heart rate above RHR from the night before
- Electrodermal activity from the day before based on EDA Scan app (if available)"

"vo2max_learn_more_content" : "The cardio fitness score is an estimate of your VO2 max, which is the maximum amount of oxygen your body can use during exercise. It tells you how well your body uses oxygen when you’re working out at your hardest. 

 Improving the intensity and consistency of your exercise over time can help increase your score. To check the intensity of your workouts, view your heart rate zones. To keep up consistency, you can set goals for how many times you work out per week. 

 Fitbit estimates your cardio fitness score based on your resting heart rate, age, self-reported sex, height, weight, and running efficiency (which becomes available after enough data is tracked from your runs).  

 Your running efficiency is the ratio between your running speed and heart rate and is meant to reflect the result of how hard you pushed yourself during a run. 

 This estimate becomes more accurate if you wear your Fitbit device while sleeping and exercising.  

"

"health_connect_onboarding_body_pre_setup_hc_installed" : " To help you stay on top of all your goals, Fitbit can now write data to Health Connect so you can access it from the other apps you use.

 How it works

 Fitbit can write data like your workouts, sleep, and heart rate to Health Connect. You can choose which data you want Fitbit to write to your device.

 Data in Health Connect is stored on your device, and other apps you’ve set up with Health Connect will be able to access this data. How these apps use the data will vary depending on the app, but each app should explain how they use your data.

 Managing your data

 Data from your Fitbit account that you choose to share with Health Connect will be stored on your device.

 Deleting data in the Fitbit app won’t affect the data in Health Connect. To delete data stored in Health Connect, go to your Fitbit settings Health Connect > Manage access. You can also manage Health Connect data in your phone’s settings.

 You can change the data Fitbit shares with Health Connect, or turn this feature off, from your Fitbit app settings. Turning off this feature won’t delete any data. "

CREATE VIEW `presets_with_mutations_applied` AS -- existing presets with mutations applied
    WITH combined_presets as (
      SELECT PresetEntity.id, COALESCE(PresetMutationEntity.title, PresetEntity.title) as title, PresetEntity.isCustom, PresetEntity.isSelected, COALESCE(PresetMutationEntity.tileIds, PresetEntity.tileIds) as tileIds
      FROM PresetEntity
      LEFT JOIN PresetMutationEntity ON PresetEntity.id = PresetMutationEntity.id

      UNION
      -- add newly created custom presets not yet in PresetsEntity
      SELECT PresetMutationEntity.*
      FROM PresetMutationEntity
      LEFT JOIN PresetEntity ON PresetMutationEntity.id = PresetEntity.id
      WHERE PresetEntity.id IS NULL
    )

    -- apply select mutation on all the presets
    SELECT combined_presets.id, combined_presets.title, combined_presets.isCustom, combined_presets.tileIds,
      CASE
         WHEN SelectPresetMutation.selectedPresetId = combined_presets.id THEN 1
         WHEN SelectPresetMutation.selectedPresetId is not combined_presets.id and EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM SelectPresetMutation) THEN 0
         ELSE combined_presets.isSelected
      END AS isSelected
    FROM combined_presets
    LEFT JOIN SelectPresetMutation on combined_presets.id = SelectPresetMutation.selectedPresetId

playstore_details.title: Fitbit
playstore_details.description:
See the big picture on your health and fitness journey with the Fitbit app. Find easy ways to get active, sleep better, stress less and eat healthier.

Track the stats you care about across health, fitness and sleep, and change your goals as your routines evolve. Stay motivated with energizing workout content for your body and mind. See how far you’ve come with a glance at your personal goal progress and how you stack up to friends and family. Unlock even more possibilities when you sync up with a wearable device like Fitbit tracker or smartwatch and see how your activity, sleep, nutrition and stress all fit together.

GET MORE ACTIVE: See how small moves add up by using your smartphone to track steps and distance—or pair with a Fitbit tracker or Wear OS by Google smartwatch to record your heart rate, Active Zone Minutes, calories burned and more. Leverage tiles and complications to easily access your stats.It’s a fitness planner in your pocket: Use the app as a diary to set goals and track your progress. Plus, that motivation you’ve been looking for is right in the app. Bring the gym home with a curated list of audio and video workouts that you can do at your own pace, right from your living room.* You’ll find sessions for HIIT, cardio, strength, running, biking, yoga and more.

TRACK YOUR HEART HEALTH: Understand your overall health by using your watch or tracker to keep tabs on your heart rate 24/7. Monitor your heart rhythm and see your resting heart rate trends, plus time spent in heart rate zones during workouts.

SLEEP BETTER: Find sleep tools to help you learn about your sleep quality and improve it—from  measuring your sleep duration and sleep stages to understanding your restless time. Set reminders for bedtime and wake-up time to keep your sleeping schedule managed.

STRESS LESS: Listen to audio sessions to lessen stress and improve your mood. Use mindfulness to start your day a better way, find moments of calm and set intentions with meditation or get help falling asleep with breathing exercises and relaxing sounds.*

EAT SMARTER: Keep your diet in check with easy-to-use tools for setting goals. Tracking meals and logging food & water intake lets you see if you’re getting enough protein, fat, fiber and carbs on your way to managing your weight and overall health.

EVEN MORE WITH FITBIT PREMIUM: Upgrade to Fitbit Premium and get all the guidance, insights and inspiration you need to take your workout routine to the next level.

• Your Daily Readiness Score helps you understand when it’s time to go all out and when it’s time for rest & recovery—plus, you’ll get recommended workouts based on your body’s needs.
• Get the support you need across a whole library of workouts to keep your mind and body fit—from strength training, HIIT and cycling to dance cardio, yoga, meditation and more—led by Fitbit’s expert trainers who are ready to coach.
• Perfect your mindfulness practice with a full library of sessions that calm anxiety, prep for sleep and even help you meditate while walking.
• Find new ways to rest & recover with your Sleep Score. Plus, check out your sleep patterns and monthly trends in your Sleep Profile.
• Feed your appetite with access to easy, healthy recipes to help you reach your nutrition goals and bring your wellness full circle.


*A Fitbit Premium subscription is required to access the full content library.

Some Fitbit devices let you handle calls and texts right from your wrist so permissions might be required during setup.

Ensure that these permissions are required by the application.

android.permission.POST_NOTIFICATIONS (dangerous): allows an app to post notifications. - Allows an app to post notifications

android.permission.READ_CONTACTS (dangerous): read contact data - Allows an application to read all of the contact (address) data stored on your phone. Malicious applications can use this to send your data to other people.

android.permission.GET_ACCOUNTS (dangerous): list accounts - Allows access to the list of accounts in the Accounts Service.

android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE (dangerous): read/modify/delete external storage contents - Allows an application to write to external storage.

android.permission.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES (dangerous): allows reading image files from external storage. - Allows an application to read image files from external storage.

android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE (dangerous): read external storage contents - Allows an application to read from external storage.

android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION (dangerous): coarse (network-based) location - Access coarse location sources, such as the mobile network database, to determine an approximate phone location, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine approximately where you are.

android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION (dangerous): fine (GPS) location - Access fine location sources, such as the Global Positioning System on the phone, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine where you are and may consume additional battery power.

android.permission.ACCESS_BACKGROUND_LOCATION (dangerous): access location in background - Allows an app to access location in the background.

android.permission.READ_PHONE_NUMBERS (dangerous): allows reading of the device's phone number(s). - Allows read access to the device's phone number(s). This is a subset of the capabilities granted by READ_PHONE_STATE but is exposed to instant applications.

android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE (dangerous): read phone state and identity - Allows the application to access the phone features of the device. An application with this permission can determine the phone number and serial number of this phone, whether a call is active, the number that call is connected to and so on.

android.permission.ANSWER_PHONE_CALLS (dangerous): permits an app to answer incoming phone calls. - Allows the app to answer an incoming phone call.

android.permission.CALL_PHONE (dangerous): directly call phone numbers - Allows the application to call phone numbers without your intervention. Malicious applications may cause unexpected calls on your phone bill. Note that this does not allow the application to call emergency numbers.

android.permission.SEND_SMS (dangerous): send SMS messages - Allows application to send SMS messages. Malicious applications may cost you money by sending messages without your confirmation.

android.permission.BLUETOOTH_SCAN (dangerous): required for discovering and pairing Bluetooth devices. - Required to be able to discover and pair nearby Bluetooth devices.

android.permission.BLUETOOTH_CONNECT (dangerous): necessary for connecting to paired Bluetooth devices. - Required to be able to connect to paired Bluetooth devices.

android.permission.READ_CALL_LOG (dangerous): grants read access to the user's call log. - Allows an application to read the user's call log.

android.permission.READ_CALENDAR (dangerous): read calendar events - Allows an application to read all of the calendar events stored on your phone. Malicious applications can use this to send your calendar events to other people.

android.permission.WRITE_CALENDAR (dangerous): add or modify calendar events and send emails to guests - Allows an application to add or change the events on your calendar, which may send emails to guests. Malicious applications can use this to erase or modify your calendar events or to send emails to guests.

android.permission.CAMERA (dangerous): take pictures and videos - Allows application to take pictures and videos with the camera. This allows the application to collect images that the camera is seeing at any time.

android.permission.ACTIVITY_RECOGNITION (dangerous): allow application to recognize physical activity - Allows an application to recognize physical activity.

android.permission.RECORD_AUDIO (dangerous): record audio - Allows application to access the audio record path.
